# Simple Expense Tracker

## Overview
Users can track personal expenses with categories and dates.

## Goals
- Help users monitor spending
- Categorize expenses
- View spending history

## User Stories
- As a user, I want to add expenses so that I can track my spending
- As a user, I want to categorize expenses so that I can see spending by category
- As a user, I want to view my expense history so that I can review past transactions

## Data Model
- `ExpenseModel`: user_id, amount, category, description, date, created_at

## API Endpoints
- `POST /api/expenses` - Create expense
- `GET /api/expenses` - List expenses (with filtering)
- `DELETE /api/expenses/{id}` - Delete expense

## UI/UX
**Pages**:
- Dashboard - List expenses + add form
- Summary - View spending by category

**Components**:
- ExpenseForm - Add expense
- ExpenseList - Display expenses
- CategorySummary - Group by category

## Technical Notes
- All endpoints require authentication
- Filter by date range and category
- Store amounts as decimals

## Out of Scope
- Recurring expenses
- Budget tracking
- Export to CSV

## Success Criteria
- [ ] User can add expense
- [ ] User can view all expenses
- [ ] User can delete expense
- [ ] Expenses grouped by category
```

